			    STPJS 286</div>
  <div class="topic">THE PROPHET ON THE SECOND COMING OF CHRIST</div>
  <div class="topic">Remarks at the Conference of the Church</div>
  <p class="std">The question has been asked, can a person not belonging to the Church bring a member before
  the high council for trial?<span class="footRef">1</span> I answer, No. If I had not actually got into this work and been called of
  God,<span class="footRef">2</span> I would back out. But I cannot back out:<span class="footRef">3</span> I have no doubt of the truth.<span class="footRef">4</span> Were I going to
  prophesy, I would say the end [of the world] would not come in 1844, 5, or 6, or in forty years.<span class="footRef">5</span>
  There are those of the rising generation<span class="footRef">6</span> who shall not taste death till Christ comes.<span class="footRef">7</span></p>
  <p class="std">I was once praying earnestly upon this subject, and a voice said unto me, &ldquo;My son, if thou livest
  until thou art eighty-five years of age, thou shalt see the face of the Son of Man.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">8</span> I was left to draw
  my own conclusions concerning this; and I took the liberty to conclude that if I did live to that time,
  He would make His appearance. But I do not say whether He will make His appearance or I shall
  go where He is. I prophesy in the name of the Lord God,<span class="footRef">9</span> and let it be written&mdash;the Son of Man will
  not come in the clouds of heaven<span class="footRef">10</span> till I am eighty-five years old.<span class="footRef">11</span> Then read the 14th chapter of
  Revelation, 6th and 7th verses&mdash;&ldquo;And I saw another angel fly in the midst of heaven, having the
  everlasting gospel to preach unto them that dwell on the earth, and to every nation, and kindred, and
  tongue, and people, saying with a loud voice, Fear God and give glory to Him, for the hour of His
  judgment is come.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">12</span> And Hosea, 6th chapter, After two days,<span class="footRef">13</span> etc.,&mdash;2,520 years; which brings it
  to 1890. The coming of the Son of Man<span class="footRef">14</span> never will be&mdash;never can be till the judgments spoken of
  for this hour are poured out:<span class="footRef">15</span> which judgments are commenced. Paul says, &ldquo;Ye are the children of
  the light, and not of the darkness, that that day should overtake you as a thief in the night.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">16</span> It is not
  the design of the Almighty to come upon the earth and crush it and grind it to powder,<span class="footRef">17</span> but he will
  reveal it to His servants the prophets.<span class="footRef">18</span></p>
  <p class="std">Judah must return,<span class="footRef">19</span> Jerusalem must be rebuilt,<span class="footRef">20</span> and the temple,<span class="footRef">21</span> and water come out from
  under the temple,<span class="footRef">22</span> and the waters of the Dead Sea be healed.<span class="footRef">23</span> It will take some time to rebuild the
  walls of the city and the temple, &amp;c.; and all this must be done before the Son of Man will make His
  appearance. There will be wars and rumors of wars,<span class="footRef">24</span> signs in the heavens</p>
